cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper deals with deep neural networks and their connections, specifically in the context of computer vision tasks such as semantic segmentation and visual recognition. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the efficiency and scalability of the proposed Log-DenseNet architecture, which suggests relevance to categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of backpropagation, which is a common technique in neural networks and could place the paper in categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with semantic segmentation, which involves natural language processing, suggesting relevance to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
